Piper longum

   [8674.jpg]
   Authority L.
   Family Magnoliopsida:Magnoliidae:Piperales:Piperaceae
   Synonyms
   Common names Indian long pepper, jaborandi pepper, pippali, thippali,
   piper, pepper long, Piperis Langi Fructus
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 8674

   Notes
   Habitat: The plant thrives in a hot moist climate, it occurs along
   streams and grows among bushes in many parts of south and east India.
   It is a native of the Indo-Malaysian region. It grows widely in the
   tropical rain forests of India, Nepal, Indonesia, Malaysia, Sri Lanka,
   Rhio, Timor and the Philippines.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
